# Two-repo layout (set up 2026-04-27):
#
#   - This (root) repo pushes to github.com/<you>/<your-private-mirror> —
#     the canonical, unredacted source of truth. Includes private/
#     contents (DEPLOYMENT_INVENTORY.md, DASHBOARD_INVENTORY.md, etc.).
#
#   - public/ has its own .git pushing to github.com/you/kpc3-ai-bot —
#     the sanitized, public-safe subset. sync_public.sh runs sed-based
#     redactions when copying selected files from root into public/.
#
# Files matching the patterns below are excluded from the private repo
# entirely. Secrets must never reach ANY cloud, even the private one.

# public/ has its own git. Not tracked from this repo.
public/

# Secrets and credentials — never to any remote, even the private repo.
# (No leading slash — these patterns match anywhere in the tree, including
# private/config.json and private/kpc3_ssh_key.)
config.json
*.key
*_key
*_key.pub
kpc3_ssh_key*
.env
.env.*

# Claude Code: per-agent ephemeral worktrees. settings.local.json IS tracked.
.claude/worktrees/

# Logs
*.log

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Editor / IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~
